table.title: High - Temperature Superconductivity

query: Summarize the high - temperature superconductors with notation of Hg - 1212 and Hg - 1223.
summary: The two high-temperature superconductors with notation of Hg-1212 and Hg-1223 notably belong to the family of cuprates. These two superconducting materials contain the formula HgBa2CaCu2O6 and HgBa2Ca2Cu3O8, respectively. The first material, Hg-1212, has a critical temperature (Tc) of 128 K and two copper–oxygen (Cu–O) planes in its unit cell. The other material,Hg-1223, has a higher Tc of 134 K and three Cu–O planes in its unit cell.

query: What were the ages of the winners of Miss New Hampshire Teen USA between the years 2000 and 2010, and how did the age vary during this period?

In 2000, Kristen O'Neil from Manchester win at age of 17, and in 2010, Morgan Lucas, also from Manchester, win at age of 18.
